# Colophon

This website is a collection of static HTML pages generated by a custom
[site generator][ssg]. It is a VM on "someone else's computer" running
[OpenBSD][]. The pages are served by [relayd][], and [httpd][]. 
The entire content of the site can be found in a [git repository](https://gith
ub.com/e-zk/site).

A [hidden service][hiddenservices] mirror of this site is available and can be
accessed at the following onion address: 
[64wv2uqwjacqer7z5d6ooqgrvjwlioizmo7hgmxm7zxerbvgnoqhafid.onion](http://64wv2u
qwjacqer7z5d6ooqgrvjwlioizmo7hgmxm7zxerbvgnoqhafid.onion).

[ssg]: https://github.com/e-zk/site-gen/
[OpenBSD]: https://openbsd.org/
[relayd]: https://man.openbsd.org/relayd
[httpd]: https://man.openbsd.org/httpd
[vis]: https://github.com/martanne/vis
[hiddenservices]: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tor_(network)#Onion_services
[djot]: https://djot.net/

Posts are edited in the [vis editor][] as Markdown, or more recently, [djot][]
files.  
In the footer of most pages, you can open the plaintext representation. I try
to keep the text width under 80 characters for consistency.

## Design

The site's design is inspired by many other personal sites, too many to
remember. Inspiration has also been taken from any number of sites on
[Dead Simple Sites](https://deadsimplesites.com/).

Code font is [Commit Mono](https://commitmono.com/).

[CSS](/style.css) is hand-written by yours truly.
